WEBVTT

1
00:00:37.994 --> 00:00:39.295
Did you sleep well?

2
00:00:42.735 --> 00:00:44.335
Your eyes are swollen.

3
00:00:50.075 --> 00:00:51.445
Don't cry from now on.

4
00:00:53.674 --> 00:00:54.714
Promise?

5
00:00:58.445 --> 00:00:59.714
I promise.

6
00:01:02.115 --> 00:01:03.354
Aren't you hungry?

7
00:01:03.585 --> 00:01:04.685
I am.

8
00:01:15.194 --> 00:01:18.735
The house is a little old. It must have been cold last night.

9
00:01:18.735 --> 00:01:21.575
No, the floor was really warm.

10
00:01:21.804 --> 00:01:23.974
It wasn't cold at all thanks to the covers you gave us.

11
00:01:24.944 --> 00:01:28.674
We neither have a television nor computer. You must have been bored.

12
00:01:29.444 --> 00:01:31.314
We don't own much.

13
00:01:31.745 --> 00:01:33.844
- Please understand. - It's fine.

14
00:01:34.245 --> 00:01:36.915
- Thank you for the meal. - Thank you.

15
00:01:36.915 --> 00:01:38.025
Eat up.

16
00:01:42.094 --> 00:01:43.224
What do you want to eat?

17
00:01:43.394 --> 00:01:44.525
You should eat what you want.

18
00:01:53.804 --> 00:01:54.875
Eat up.

19
00:01:58.745 --> 00:02:00.575
- Is it delicious? - Yes.

20
00:02:14.954 --> 00:02:17.024
You have such...

21
00:02:17.255 --> 00:02:19.565
big eyes and nose.

22
00:02:19.864 --> 00:02:21.494
You have pretty lips too.

23
00:02:21.665 --> 00:02:25.964
I was wondering how someone could look so pretty.

24
00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:28.475
But now, I remember seeing you on television.

25
00:02:29.374 --> 00:02:32.445
Thank you for everything. Thanks to you, we slept well...

26
00:02:32.674 --> 00:02:36.244
and had a great breakfast. I heard the car has been fixed too.

27
00:02:37.345 --> 00:02:39.885
We won't bother you anymore.

28
00:02:40.485 --> 00:02:42.285
You speak so kindly.

29
00:02:43.714 --> 00:02:46.855
I didn't know that young people could be like that.

30
00:02:47.355 --> 00:02:48.424
Pardon?

31
00:02:49.195 --> 00:02:51.165
I meant your husband.

32
00:02:52.295 --> 00:02:53.394
Why?

33
00:02:53.565 --> 00:02:55.864
Yesterday, he was standing there...

34
00:02:55.964 --> 00:02:58.105
in the dark, anxious and worried.

35
00:02:59.065 --> 00:03:00.904
- Yesterday? - Yes.

36
00:03:01.075 --> 00:03:02.505
Before you both came in.

37
00:03:03.334 --> 00:03:07.674
He came first and begged us to let you sleep for a night.

38
00:03:08.374 --> 00:03:10.415
I couldn't refuse.

39
00:03:10.945 --> 00:03:12.644
He said he didn't need to sleep...

40
00:03:13.385 --> 00:03:15.654
and that he just needed to get his wife a place to sleep.

41
00:03:21.695 --> 00:03:24.095
We are not from here,

42
00:03:24.325 --> 00:03:27.295
and there aren't any young people here. So we were scared at first.

43
00:03:28.235 --> 00:03:30.795
But he seemed so urgent,

44
00:03:31.065 --> 00:03:32.605
so we let him in.

45
00:03:32.605 --> 00:03:33.834
Thank you.

46
00:03:34.374 --> 00:03:36.505
You chose well.

47
00:03:38.005 --> 00:03:39.744
Yes. He's kind.

48
00:03:39.804 --> 00:03:41.274
He's not just kind.

49
00:03:41.744 --> 00:03:43.614
He has such a big heart.

50
00:04:23.085 --> 00:04:24.155
Excuse me.

51
00:04:24.554 --> 00:04:25.624
Yes?

52
00:04:27.285 --> 00:04:30.424
I'm sorry, but may I borrow your car for a moment?

53
00:04:30.624 --> 00:04:32.165
I need to visit the village.

54
00:04:33.725 --> 00:04:35.564
Your wife is here.

55
00:04:35.965 --> 00:04:37.465
You won't run away, right?

56
00:04:38.264 --> 00:04:40.205
Of course not. I'll be quick.

57
00:05:12.465 --> 00:05:14.634
Oh, my. This fits perfectly.

58
00:05:17.775 --> 00:05:19.645
Gosh. What is this?

59
00:05:25.884 --> 00:05:27.085
Thank you.

60
00:05:27.855 --> 00:05:30.485
For a young person, you're really nice...

61
00:05:30.485 --> 00:05:31.785
and pick up things quickly.

62
00:05:32.254 --> 00:05:34.494
How did you even think of this?

63
00:06:29.215 --> 00:06:31.514
Oh, there he is.

64
00:06:46.824 --> 00:06:54.775
(The 14th  : Before Sunrise)

65
00:06:54.775 --> 00:06:57.535
(The 14th story: Before Sunrise)

66
00:07:00.845 --> 00:07:03.345
Does a Sa Ho Sung work here?

67
00:07:03.645 --> 00:07:07.244
Sa Ho Sung? I've never heard that name before.

68
00:07:07.585 --> 00:07:09.684
Do you know "Love Cosmos"?

69
00:07:09.684 --> 00:07:11.924
It's someone who draws cosmos flowers.

70
00:07:11.924 --> 00:07:13.225
I don't.

71
00:07:13.225 --> 00:07:15.655
Wasn't a box of mandarins delivered here from Jeju Island?

72
00:07:15.655 --> 00:07:16.754
No.

73
00:07:19.994 --> 00:07:23.364
If you ever hear of or meet Sa Ho Sung or Love Cosmos,

74
00:07:23.364 --> 00:07:25.304
please give me a call.

75
00:07:25.835 --> 00:07:26.835
Sure.

76
00:07:38.614 --> 00:07:41.514
Hi. I checked again, and it's that school.

77
00:07:41.985 --> 00:07:44.054
It's the only school with that name.

78
00:07:46.054 --> 00:07:48.254
Okay. Thanks.

79
00:07:50.924 --> 00:07:53.264
I think this is the right neighborhood.

80
00:07:55.194 --> 00:07:57.595
- Is it someone else? - No.

81
00:07:58.235 --> 00:07:59.934
I bet she ran away.

82
00:08:00.564 --> 00:08:03.374
Mom and Dad lost her right in front of their eyes many times.

83
00:08:04.345 --> 00:08:08.045
Since we're here, let's ask around the village.

84
00:08:11.744 --> 00:08:13.884
Her name is Sa Ho Sung.

85
00:08:13.884 --> 00:08:15.514
She's in her late 30s.

86
00:08:15.915 --> 00:08:18.485
Sa Ho Sung? A woman in her late 30s?

87
00:08:18.485 --> 00:08:21.624
This isn't a city center. There are no women in their 30s.

88
00:08:21.624 --> 00:08:23.095
There are only old people.

89
00:08:25.795 --> 00:08:28.634
Wait, there is one.

90
00:08:28.835 --> 00:08:31.905
A young woman lives behind the sacred tree.

91
00:08:31.934 --> 00:08:33.965
- Okay? - Soo Yeon? Soo Hyun?

92
00:08:34.134 --> 00:08:35.705
Yes, it's Lee Soo Hyun.

93
00:08:36.435 --> 00:08:38.274
She's the only young lady.

94
00:08:43.114 --> 00:08:44.845
I love it.

95
00:08:44.845 --> 00:08:49.154
I'll frame it and hang it up in a sunlit corner.

96
00:08:53.555 --> 00:08:55.725
(Community Center)

97
00:09:01.195 --> 00:09:03.164
- Hello. - Welcome.

98
00:09:03.164 --> 00:09:06.965
I brought this for all of you to drink.

99
00:09:06.965 --> 00:09:08.774
Here you go.

100
00:09:08.774 --> 00:09:10.534
- Here. - This looks tasty.

101
00:09:10.534 --> 00:09:12.945
Have you heard of Sa Ho Sung?

102
00:09:12.945 --> 00:09:15.014
- Sa Ho Sun? - Sa Ho Sun?

103
00:09:15.014 --> 00:09:17.114
Sa Ho Sung, not Sa Ho Sun.

104
00:09:17.114 --> 00:09:19.914
- She doesn't live here. - Never heard the name before.

105
00:09:19.914 --> 00:09:21.654
I don't know her.

106
00:09:21.654 --> 00:09:23.715
Is Sa Ho Sung a person's name?

107
00:09:23.715 --> 00:09:25.955
There's no one with that name here.

108
00:09:26.355 --> 00:09:28.425
- You don't know? - Go to that room,

109
00:09:28.425 --> 00:09:31.595
and ask if the men know her.

110
00:09:33.024 --> 00:09:35.235
Hello, how are you?

111
00:09:35.235 --> 00:09:37.394
I'd like to ask you something.

112
00:09:37.394 --> 00:09:41.435
Do any of you know of a Sa Ho Sung who lives here?

113
00:09:41.435 --> 00:09:43.735
- Who? - Sa Ho Sung.

114
00:09:43.735 --> 00:09:47.044
Sa Ho Sung? I don't know that name.

115
00:09:47.044 --> 00:09:50.114
What's the name of the girl who lives behind the sacred tree?

116
00:09:51.144 --> 00:09:53.345
Her name is Soo Hyun.

117
00:09:53.345 --> 00:09:56.284
- Lee Soo Hyun. - Is it?

118
00:09:57.254 --> 00:09:58.254
Checkmate.

119
00:09:58.254 --> 00:10:01.794
Hello, ma'am, can I ask you something?

120
00:10:01.794 --> 00:10:05.225
Do you know if a Sa Ho Sung lives in the area?

121
00:10:05.725 --> 00:10:07.095
I don't know.

122
00:10:07.095 --> 00:10:09.894
She's a young woman.

123
00:10:09.894 --> 00:10:11.435
I don't know.

124
00:10:12.605 --> 00:10:14.835
Sir, can I ask a question?

125
00:10:14.835 --> 00:10:17.435
Do you know if a Sa Ho Sung lives nearby?

126
00:10:17.435 --> 00:10:18.774
I don't know.

127
00:10:18.774 --> 00:10:21.774
Sa... Sa? I don't know.

128
00:10:21.774 --> 00:10:23.414
Sa Ho Sung?

129
00:10:37.794 --> 00:10:40.595
You're in no situation to be in...

130
00:10:40.595 --> 00:10:42.634
"My Wife's Ghost Marriage".

131
00:10:43.034 --> 00:10:44.534
If the chief finds out,

132
00:10:44.534 --> 00:10:46.735
he would bow to you in the lobby.

133
00:10:46.735 --> 00:10:48.004
That would be great.

134
00:10:48.935 --> 00:10:50.105
Let's not do it.

135
00:10:50.575 --> 00:10:52.244
Tell the director you can't do it.

136
00:10:52.244 --> 00:10:54.044
What's the point in not working?

137
00:10:54.044 --> 00:10:56.175
You want to die counting money.

138
00:10:56.175 --> 00:10:58.345
Is it because I'm always talking about money?

139
00:10:58.345 --> 00:11:01.154
No. I want to make a living too.

140
00:11:03.355 --> 00:11:06.055
I'm the housewives' EXO.

141
00:11:08.425 --> 00:11:11.494
I really think this is the wrong move.

142
00:11:15.095 --> 00:11:17.735
Wait. Think about it again.

143
00:11:17.735 --> 00:11:20.634
I'll be treated well and paid well. Isn't that just great?

144
00:11:28.044 --> 00:11:29.914
A meeting with Anthony?

145
00:11:29.914 --> 00:11:32.685
He's past his season and good for nothing.

146
00:11:32.685 --> 00:11:34.754
He's not even Sa Jin Jin's husband anymore,

147
00:11:34.754 --> 00:11:37.514
and his acting isn't that great. Why should I meet him?

148
00:11:37.514 --> 00:11:40.325
Don't you know we cast rookie actor Kim Min Chul?

149
00:11:40.524 --> 00:11:42.425
He said he'd come in for a meeting.

150
00:11:43.154 --> 00:11:45.595
I couldn't think of an excuse in time. I apologize.

151
00:11:45.595 --> 00:11:47.864
We have to make small talk if we meet him.

152
00:11:47.864 --> 00:11:50.534
Do you know how exhausting that is?

153
00:11:57.805 --> 00:12:01.414
I got your hopes up only to return to Seoul empty-handed.

154
00:12:01.914 --> 00:12:02.914
Sorry.

155
00:12:03.675 --> 00:12:05.445
I should apologize.

156
00:12:06.114 --> 00:12:07.855
You skipped work.

157
00:12:08.855 --> 00:12:09.855
What'll you do?

158
00:12:09.855 --> 00:12:13.085
Who cares? I'm delighted to skip work.

159
00:12:18.024 --> 00:12:20.124
I wonder where she is.

160
00:12:28.874 --> 00:12:31.205
What are you looking at?

161
00:12:31.205 --> 00:12:32.904
Look at this.

162
00:12:33.805 --> 00:12:36.715
It's Sa Jin Jin. Was that photoshopped?

163
00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:39.244
No, she came to our school.

164
00:12:39.244 --> 00:12:40.345
Why?

165
00:12:41.715 --> 00:12:43.384
To find someone.

166
00:12:43.384 --> 00:12:46.355
- These mandarins are sweet. - There are more over there.

167
00:12:46.355 --> 00:12:48.994
Ms. Lee Soo Hyun had some sent from Jeju Island.

168
00:12:48.994 --> 00:12:51.124
Who's Ms. Lee?

169
00:12:51.124 --> 00:12:54.764
The art teacher who comes in to teach the kids after school.

170
00:12:56.335 --> 00:12:58.335
The teacher from Jeju Island?

171
00:12:58.335 --> 00:13:00.864
- Her name is Lee Soo Hyun? - Yes.

172
00:13:20.085 --> 00:13:21.754
A young woman...

173
00:13:22.325 --> 00:13:25.864
- lives behind the sacred tree. - Okay.

174
00:13:25.925 --> 00:13:28.634
Soo Yeon? Soo Hyun? Yes, it's Lee Soo Hyun.

175
00:13:28.634 --> 00:13:30.894
Her name is Soo Hyun.

176
00:13:30.894 --> 00:13:33.465
- Lee Soo Hyun. - Is it?

177
00:13:34.164 --> 00:13:35.475
Lee Soo Hyun.

178
00:13:39.144 --> 00:13:40.504
Lee Soo Hyun?

179
00:13:53.725 --> 00:13:55.825
(To Sa Ho Sung)

180
00:14:00.925 --> 00:14:01.994
Okay.

181
00:14:02.994 --> 00:14:05.264
I found the box. Hang on.

182
00:14:10.274 --> 00:14:12.105
Here it is.

183
00:14:13.075 --> 00:14:17.315
"To Sa Ho Sung, from Lee Soo Hyun"

184
00:14:30.394 --> 00:14:33.095
- Okay, thanks. - Sure.

185
00:14:37.735 --> 00:14:39.465
It's her love letter.

186
00:14:39.565 --> 00:14:40.835
Min Ho.

187
00:14:41.274 --> 00:14:43.134
- Min Ho! - What?

188
00:14:49.544 --> 00:14:50.914
Is something wrong?

189
00:14:50.914 --> 00:14:52.985
Yes. We're going back.

190
00:15:01.009 --> 00:15:04.241
<font color="#80ffff">[VIU Ver] E27 20th Century Boy & Girl "Before Sunrise"</font>
